# Clayworth graph: definition

The **Clayworth graph** (4032 vertices, cubic) is defined via O(1) neighbor
lookup from precomputed adjacency data. This file contains only the graph
definition and `DecidableRel` instance — no proofs, no generators, no
Sabidussi machinery. Lightweight import for files that need `clayworthGraph`.

See `Archive.ClayworthSabidussi` for the Sabidussi coset graph proof.
-/

